The paper deals with socially-aware navigation of mobile robots, which is a topic that falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves optimization techniques and decision-making algorithms, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on human-robot interaction and social norms suggests that the paper could also be classified under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses a 2D simulator and involves image processing techniques, which could potentially fall under computer vision (cs.CV).
